---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import StationFacts from '../components/StationFacts.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`${site.callsign} · ${site.name}, amateur radio`}
  description="KJ5IRQ is Joshua Ford's amateur radio station in Texas: AllStarLink, EchoLink, and the tooling that automates the node."
>
  <article>
    <header class="radio-head">
      <p class="label">The station</p>
      <h1 class="callsign-display">{site.callsign}</h1>
      <p class="page-dek">Amateur radio station of Joshua Ford, Texas.</p>
    </header>

    <section class="radio-section">
      <h2 class="meta section-heading">Station facts</h2>
      <StationFacts />
    </section>

    <section class="radio-section prose">
      <h2 class="meta section-heading">For the non-hams</h2>
      <p>
        Amateur radio is a licensed hobby where people build and operate their own communication
        systems: voice, data, and everything in between, no carrier or account required. It is the
        original decentralized network, and it still works when nothing else does.
      </p>
      <p>
        My corner of it leans toward the networked modes. AllStarLink connects radio nodes over
        the internet, which means my node is both a radio and a Linux service. That overlap is
        where most of my projects come from.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="radio-section prose">
      <h2 class="meta section-heading">The node</h2>
      <p>
        I run an AllStarLink node, and because it is also a computer, it has grown a REST API, an
        MCP server for AI agents, and a browser control panel. The full story is in
        <a href="/projects/allstar-toolchain/">the AllStar node toolchain</a> write-up.
      </p>
      <p>
        Looking for me on the air or want node details? Check
        <a href={site.qrz} rel="noopener">QRZ</a> or just
        <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>email me</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <p class="meta sign-off">73 de {site.callsign}</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .radio-head {
    padding-block: var(--space-8) var(--space-6);
  }

  .callsign-display {
    font-size: var(--size-display);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }

  .page-dek {
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: var(--size-h3);
  }

  .radio-section {
    padding-block: var(--space-6);
  }

  .section-heading {
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }

  .sign-off {
    padding-block: var(--space-7);
  }
</style>
